-- Russia’s Biggest Shoe Retailer Signs Sberbank Loan
-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 2012-05-25T05:32:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-25/russia-s-biggest-shoe-retailer-signs-sberbank-loan.html
ZAO Torgovy Dom Tsentrobuv,  Russia ’s
biggest shoe retailer, signed a 5 billion rubles ($157 million)
loan agreement with  OAO Sberbank (SBER)  until May 22, 2015, the
retailer said in a  statement  on its website.  The loan deal totals about 7.1 billion rubles ($222
million) including interest rates payable for the use of the
loan, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow at 
 msysoyeva@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  